This paper deals with dialogue state tracking and referring expression resolution tasks, which are both related to natural language processing and understanding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach using a pointer-generator network and multi-task learning, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the challenge of tracking conversational state in a multi-domain scenario, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper involves query reformulation, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
